  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Civil Society to Improve Business Respect for the Rights to Water and Sanitation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project has two main components:
1) Development of a training curriculum
a. Outcome: Training curriculum that is useful to CSOs and CBOs and that can assist communities in holding companies responsible for their water management practices.
2) Undertaking two train the trainer workshops with civil society networks
a. Outcome: Core group of civil society actors dedicated to the human right to water who understand the opportunities to engage/advocate for companies on aspects around respecting the human right to water.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">to enable civil society and community-based organizations to be able to effectively utilize the &quot;CEO Water Mandate Guidance for Companies on Respecting the Human Rights to Water and Sanitation&quot; in their campaigns focused on corporations</narrative>
  </description>
